# dashboard/.env.local.example
#
# Copy to `.env.local` and fill in.  NEVER commit `.env.local`.
#
# Two patterns are supported:
#
# 1) For LOCAL dev, set plaintext values directly:
DASHBOARD_PASSWORD=dev

# 2) For PRODUCTION (Vercel), use 1Password refs + `op run`:
# DASHBOARD_PASSWORD=op://Unite-Group-Infrastructure/DASHBOARD_PASSWORD/credential
#
# If `.env.local` contains unresolved `op://` refs and `op` CLI is not signed in,
# `dashboard/scripts/dev-env.sh` will substitute the dev password "dev" so local
# dev never silently fails with "Invalid password".

# Machine-to-machine secret (Vercel proxy -> Railway backend). Random, 30+ chars.
# PI_CEO_PASSWORD=

# Anthropic API key used by the dashboard agents
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...

# GitHub PAT for repo reads / branch pushes
# GITHUB_TOKEN=ghp_...

# Optional Telegram bot token
# TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN=

# Model override
# ANALYSIS_MODEL=claude-opus-4-7
